Calculating the areas of both of the shapes we get $A_{circle}=\pi r^2$ and $A_{square}=s^2=(r\sqrt{3})^2=3r^2$. Thus, the ratio of the area of the square to the area of the circle is $\frac{3r^2}{\pi r^2}=\frac{3\cancel{r^2}}{\pi \cancel{r^2}}=\boxed{\frac{3}{\pi}}$. The answer is \frac{3}{\pi}.

To calculate the total surface area of the cylinder, we cut off the two ends to obtain two circles of radius $3.$

