label("10",(0,0)--(0,10),W);
[/asy]

The circumference of one of the ends is $$2\pi r = 2\pi(3)=6\pi,$$ so the width of the rectangle is $6\pi.$ Therefore, the area of this rectangle is $10\times 6\pi = 60\pi.$ So the total surface area of the cylinder is $18\pi + 60\pi = \boxed{78\pi}.$ The answer is 78\pi.

